Label: Cause of Death
MOWG Recommendation: Use ICD-10 (https://platform.who.int/mortality/about/list-of-causes-and-corresponding-icd-10-codes) -- this means changing from text to inclusive categorical.

Label: Cause of Death Code
Reconciliation Notes: Should this be an exclusive categorical?  What codes are used here?
MOWG Recommendation: Use ICD-10 (https://platform.who.int/mortality/about/list-of-causes-and-corresponding-icd-10-codes) -- this means changing from text to inclusive categorical.

Label: Manner of Death
NBB permissible values (incl. null): [Not Deceased; Accidental; Homicide; Suicide; Natural; Manner of Death Undetermined; Unknown if subject is deceased or not]
Specimen Portal permissible values: [Not Deceased; Accidental; Homicide; Suicide; Natural; Manner of Death Undetermined; Unknown if subject is deceased or not]
Reconciliation Notes: What is the difference between cause of death and manner of death?
MOWG Recommendation: Use values from NBB/HSWG: these are values that indicate a determination of how the injury or disease leads to death, cause of death is the injury or disease that leads to death.
